An undisclosed amount of cash and a firearm were stolen from a security van on Tuesday morning in Kempton Park east of Johannesburg.The van owned by private security company G4S was parked outside a ShopRite store which is one of its clients. As the security team was transferring money from Shoprite to the van the team was accosted by at least two armed attackers police said. The investigation is ongoing according to Captain Jethro Mtshali of the Kempton Park SAPS. Police are currently searching for two suspects whom they believe made off with all or part of the cash that was being transferred.The attack occurred before 9 am. No one was injured and no shots were fired Mtshali said.Police have appealed to anyone with information to contact the department.